---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="HAX Principles - Vittorio's Portfolio">
  <section class="min-h-screen py-2000 px-400 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <mds-text typography="h1" class="mb-600 text-tone-neutral-01">HAX Principles</mds-text>
      <mds-text typography="detail" class="mb-1200 leading-relaxed">
        Designing transparent, predictable AI experiences following Microsoft HAX guidelines
      </mds-text>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <mds-text typography="detail" class="mb-800">
          Human-AI Experience (HAX) principles guide the design of AI systems that are transparent,
          predictable, and user-centered. These principles ensure AI enhances rather than hinders
          human capabilities.
        </mds-text>

        <mds-card class="bg-label-green-10 mb-800">
          <mds-card-content>
            <mds-text typography="h2" class="mb-400 text-tone-neutral-01"
              >Core HAX Principles</mds-text
            >
            <ul class="space-y-400 text-tone-neutral-05">
              <li>
                <strong>Make clear what the system can do</strong> - Users should understand the AI's
                capabilities and limitations.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Make clear how well the system can do what it can do</strong> - Provide confidence
                indicators and accuracy information.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Time services based on context</strong> - Deliver AI assistance at the right moment.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Show contextually relevant information</strong> - Present information that matters
                to the user's current task.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Match relevant social norms</strong> - Design AI interactions that feel natural
                and appropriate.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Mitigate social biases</strong> - Ensure AI systems are fair and inclusive.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Support efficient invocation</strong> - Make it easy for users to access AI features
                when needed.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Support efficient dismissal</strong> - Allow users to easily ignore or dismiss
                AI suggestions.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Support efficient correction</strong> - Enable users to fix AI mistakes quickly
                and easily.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Scope services when in doubt</strong> - Limit AI actions when uncertainty exists.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Make clear why the system did what it did</strong> - Provide explanations for
                AI decisions.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Remember recent interactions</strong> - Maintain context across user sessions.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Learn from user behavior</strong> - Adapt to user preferences over time.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Update and adapt cautiously</strong> - Make changes that improve rather than disrupt
                user workflows.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Encourage granular feedback</strong> - Enable users to provide specific feedback
                on AI performance.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Convey the consequences of user actions</strong> - Help users understand how their
                actions affect the AI system.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Provide global controls</strong> - Give users control over AI behavior and settings.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Notify users about changes</strong> - Keep users informed about system updates
                and changes.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </mds-card-content>
        </mds-card>

        <mds-text typography="detail">
          <a
            href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/haxtoolkit/ai-guidelines/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-label-green-04 hover:underline"
          >
            Learn more about Microsoft HAX guidelines →
          </a>
        </mds-text>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-1200">
        <a href={baseUrl} class="text-label-green-04 hover:underline">← Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
